The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Manager found dead
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Manager found dead
                            
	Krishnagar, June 3: A manager of a food products factory in Sodepur, on the citys northern fringes, was found dead on a field near Aranghata station in Nadia this morning.         
	Shyamal Basaks throat had been slit. A bachelor, Basak, 32, a commerce graduate, had been working in the plant for seven years.        
	Talu Sarkar, 37, whose husband died five years ago, has been arrested. The woman from Aranghata, 70km from Calcutta, works in the packaging section of Basaks plant.         
	Basak had an affair with the widow. She had borrowed money from him for her daughters marriage, a police officer said.        
	Nurse body: The body of Aparna Ghosh, 35, a Burdwan Medical College and Hospital nurse, was found floating in a tank near the hospital last night.                                                                                                                                                                         
